    "• an oracle inequality with rates 1/ √ n. Note that an empirical inequality was part of the proof.",
    "• an oracle inequality with rate 1/n.",
    "It is important to note that the proof we will propose does not directly involve any empirical inequality.",
    "(The reader might remark that (4.6) in the proof below is almost an empirical inequality, but the term r(θ *) is not empirical as it depends on the unknown θ *).",
